{
  "texts": [
    "The aim of PLSs is to present advanced constructs to the end-users who do not necessarily have the knowledge to comprehend the complete research article 37, and maintaining the readability level at or below the 6th grade standard is critical to avoid excluding a large proportion of the intended audience.",
    "These findings align with studies by Banić et al.",
    "32 and Karačić et al.",
    "24, which also found that around 15 years of education was needed to comprehend a Cochrane PLS.",
    "Moreover, when simplifying language in PLSs, writers should be careful not to change the conclusions of the PLSs, so further study is needed on whether downgrading the reading levels creates changes in the quality of the message in a PLS."
  ]
}